untries jsw steel is an indian steel company owned by the jsw group based in mumbai maharashtra india jsw steel after merger of ispat steel has become indias second largest private sector steel company the current installed capacity is  mtpa a  billion conglomerate with presence across india usa south america  africa the jsw group is a part of the op jindal group with strong footprints across core economic sectors namely steel energy infrastructure cement ventures and sports jsws history can be traced back to  when the jindal group acquired piramal steel limited which operated a mini steel mill at tarapur in maharashtra and renamed it as jindal iron and steel company jisco the group set up its first steel plant in  at vasind near mumbai soon after it acquired piramal steel ltd which operated a mini steel mill at tarapur in maharashtra the jindals who had wide experience in the steel industry renamed it as jindal iron and steel co ltd jisco jindal vijayanagar steel ltd jvsl was set up in  with its plant located at toranagallu in the bellaryhospet area of karnataka the heart of the highgrade iron ore belt and spread over  acres  km of land it is just  kilometres  mi from bangalore and is well connected with both the goa and chennai port in  jisco and jvsl merged to form jsw steel ltd jsw steel has also formed a joint venture for steel plant in georgia the company has also tied up with jfe steel corp japan for manufacturing the high grade automotive steel the company has also acquired mining assets in republic of chile united states and mozambique contents  history  facilities  vijayanagar works  salem works  dolvi works  vasind works  tarapur works  kalmeshwar works  products  competitors  references  external links historyedit in  jindal vijayanagar steel jvsl was set up with its plant located at toranagallu in the bellaryhospet area in the state of karnataka the heart of the highgrade iron ore belt and spread over  acres  km of land over a decade it also set up a pl