works is poised at the forefront of the indian stainless steel industry and its strategic location is perfect for capitalizing on this the plants located just outside the thriving hub of mumbai city are close to the ports perfect for international shipment and at the hub of the indian highway system for domestic transport we believe that in staying true to our motto of inner vision global action we can maintain our relationships with all our stakeholders grow continuously and match the worlds best in stainless steel profile india steel works limited was listed on the bombay stock exchange in the year  currently about half of the companys issued equity capital is held by the promoters and the rest is with the general public bodies corporate and foreign institutions the company has over  shareholders the operations of the company are governed by an experienced board of directors comprising of executives independent directors and major shareholders supported by highly qualified  skilled personnel with intensive experience in the stainless steel industry the company employs over a  staff and workers across  factories our total production capacity is  tons per annum the factories are spread across a land area of  square meters operations are run out of a head office in the business hub of mumbai with plants around the city at navi mumbai savroli  khopoli corporate governance corporate governance at india steel is focused on fair business practices with all stake holders our business style is transparent and marked by integrity in all our dealings as befits a publicly listed company a tailormade enterprise resources program has been successfully implemented to tighten controls increase efficiencies and monitor costs employees from bottomup are continuously being trained to ensure success of the program continuous appraisal at the competencies of personnel in line with job requirements is carried out to facilitate higher levels of output and productivity sustainability at india steel works our goal is to achieve zero discharge at our plants and keep our carbon footprint light at india steel works our goal is to achieve zero discharge at our plants and keep our carbon footprint light factories are equipped with primary and secondary treatment systems to capture and clean the fumes generated during steelmaking the waste gases from the melting furnaces and convertor are dedusted in the primary treatment system and any such gases that escape are captured through the secondary treatment system which purifies them  finally emits clean air similarly the fumes generated from the annealing and pickling processes are scrubbed and sent to effluent treatment plants we have stateoftheart effluent treatment facilities which convert the chemical discharge into clean water to be recycled and used in the various processes the dust generated from the extraction is sent to an independent  certified solid waste management facility for final treatment and disposal history  the company is founded by mr harbanslal gupta as india steel industries with a plant for manufacturing bright bars  several other products in central mumbai with a capacity of about  tons per annum  the company narrows its focus to production of bright bars  emphas is shifted from carbon steels to stainless steels  isibars pvt ltd isi standing for india steel industries is floated and sets up in turbhe navi mumbai for the manufacture of stainless steel bright bars  isibars lists on the bombay stock exchange with an initial public offer which is heavily oversubscribed  isibars integrates backwards into steel melting and hotrolling by settingup a steelplant in khopoli near mumbai  major expansion plan kicks off to modernize the steelplant expand capacity and increase product range  bright bar division started at khopoli and bright bar capacity at navi mumbai is increased  a wire division is started under the name isinox steels ltd at savroli near mumbai  a stateoftheart bar and rod rolling mill is bought from pomini spa now siemens va of italy  commissioned successfully  the founder and chairman of the company mr harbanslal gupta passes away ashwin gupta is appointed executive chairman and sudhir gupta as managing director carrying forward the founding vision of a company committed to excellence  new furnaces and combined drawing machines are added to increase finishing capacity  improve quality  steelmelting capacity is increased to achieve full potential of hotrolling facilities  bright bar capacity in navi mumbai shifted and merged into the khopoli facilities welcome to khira steel works pvt ltd home product company profile management r  dqc factory tour services testimonials contact info   we at khira are basically coming from business community and having a well groomed and dedicated people with adequeate qualification technical and commercial expierience the motto of the organization is serve the customer in the best way we have well anchored brand image and good will in the market by virtue of being in the trade since last  years our customer base is very strong and varying we manufacture all our products from the best and prime raw materials since we do not compromise in the quality and therefore we are proud that our customers are happy with us and that they place repeat orders we give equal important to service to clients with flexible and adjustable attitude to the exact requirement of customers we are in a position to meet the just need of the client customisation is our specialization in execution of orders   home  product  company profile  management  rdqc  factory tour  services  testimonials  contact info copyright   khira steel works pvtltd all rights reserved steel authority of india limited sail  company profile and swot analysis timetric login  my basket  eur gbp steel authority of india limited sail  company profile and swot analysis timetric december   pages timetric report id  summary table of contents synopsistimetrics steel